---
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: 'Common Guide'
description: 'Eleventy starter using modern CSS, fluid type, fluid spacing, flexible layout and progressive enhancement.'
blog:
  title: 'Updates'
  intro: "I'm showing the last 4 blog posts, but there might be more!"
---

<div class="wrapper">
  <header class="full | section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-primary)">
    <div class="section__inner flow region">
      <h1 class="text-center" style="color: var(--color-light);">{{ title }}</h1>
    </div>
    {% svg "divider/waves", null, "divider" %}
  </header>

  <article class="full | region">
    <div class="prose wrapper flow">
      <h2 id="an-eleventy-starter">Imagine if you didn't have to write all your policy from scratch? </h2>
      <p>
        Common.Guide is a collaborative repository of "decent" policy, governance practice and ideas for radical community organisation. This is an open source project and we encourage contributions. Governance work is difficult and dry, we believe the work should flow on and benefit all!
      </p>
      <p>
        <button><a href="#" data-button-variant="primary" class="button">See the repository</a></button>
        <button><a href="#" data-button-variant="secondary" class="button">Get started</a></button>
    </p>
      <p>Common.Guide also acts as a portal for the whole community ecosystem to collaborate on policy and governance design. This increases the capacity, knowledge, and the access to ideas and is a cool instance of building our Solidarity Economy.

We use fancy Version Control Systems to track changes to our policy templates over time, and offer variations for different particular use cases. <br><strong>See our managed curations below or (link) explore others!</strong></p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="prose wrapper flow">
      <h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>
      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="feature |  region region-space-l">
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">
          {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
					{% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 4) %}
            {% set headingLevel = "h3" %}
						{% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
					{% endeach %}
        </custom-masonry>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
